Port of Engagement Address: [56 Millicent Rd]
There is a note at the end of this record stating that 'G. Sherard' was 'discharged on the grounds of sickness viz: Cellulitis of the right hand, Injured in the ship's service'.
There is an attached official note with the record, regarding this seaman. It relates to how he was landed in hospital at Suez, due to 'Sickness' and 'Stricture'.

There is an attached official note with the record, regarding a J. Farwell, which appears to be a mis-spelling of this seaman, as the dates and notes seem to fit. The document relates how he was landed in hospital at Suez, due to 'Sickness' and 'Asthma'.
